Part A: Conversions (Customary)

72 inches = ___ feet

5 gallons = ___ quarts

7 yards = ___ feet

40 ounces = ___ pounds

Part B: Conversions (Metric)

3,000 milliliters = ___ liters

2.5 kilograms = ___ grams

9 meters = ___ centimeters

0.8 kilometers = ___ meters

Part C: Measuring & Comparing

Write >, <, or =.

4 cups ___ 2 pints

600 g ___ 0.6 kg

90 minutes ___ 1 hour

2.5 L ___ 2,300 mL

Part D: Elapsed Time

School starts at 8:15 AM and ends at 3:05 PM.
How long is the school day?

A TV show begins at 7:42 PM and ends at 8:25 PM.
How long is the episode?

Part E: Graphing & Data Interpretation

Use this data for a bar graph or answer directly:
Students’ favorite sports:

Soccer: 18

Basketball: 12

Baseball: 9

Swimming: 15

Which sport is most popular?

How many students were surveyed total?

How many more students chose Soccer than Baseball?

Part F: Measurement Word Problems

A container holds 4.5 liters of juice. Each bottle holds 750 mL.
How many full bottles can be filled?

A gardener has 21 feet of fencing. Each section of his garden requires 3.5 feet.
How many sections can he create?

A tank holds 55 gallons of water. If it leaks 2.5 gallons every hour, how long until it is empty?

Part G: Challenge Questions

Explain your reasoning.

Why is converting in the metric system easier than in the customary system?

A student claims that 1 kilogram is “basically the same as 1,000 pounds.”
Explain why this is incorrect using unit reasoning.